China Power Investment Aims to Spend $6 Billion on Guinea Bauxite Refinery

-- B y   O u g n a   C a m a r a
-- 
2011-08-20T14:29:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-20/china-power-investment-to-spend-6-billion-on-guinea-refineries.html
China Power Investment Corp. will
spend $6 billion to develop bauxite and alumina refineries at
Boffa in  Guinea , according to a statement from the president’s
office.  The Beijing-based energy company will also build a port to
remove ore from the area, President  Alpha Conde ’s office said in
the statement, citing China Power Vice President Yu Dehui.  The facilities will initially produce 12 million tons
annually of bauxite, used to make aluminum, along with 4 million
tons of alumina, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ougna Camara in Conakry at 
 ocamara@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mike Harrison at 
 mharrison5@bloomberg.net  